## **âœ… MANDATORY REQUIREMENTS**

### **1. Coding Style - Personal Programming Style**

- âœ… **Incremental Development**: Code in small parts, commit multiple times over time (like humans code gradually, NOT entire project at once)
- âœ… **Iterative Refinement**: Build basic â†’ Test â†’ Improve â†’ Refactor (NOT perfect code first try - this is AI signature)
- âœ… **Manual Git Control**: ABSOLUTELY NO auto-commit, let developer decide commit message, timing, and staging
- âœ… **Thoughtful Comments**: Write comments in Vietnamese or English naturally, explain "why" not just "what"
- âœ… **Personal Patterns**: Use consistent naming conventions, code structure, formatting style throughout project (learn from existing code)
- âœ… **Natural Imperfections**: Allow reasonable "imperfections" (like refactor later, optimize later) - like real human work

### **2. Design Approach - Design Methodology**

- âœ… **Design-First Thinking**: Create mockups/sketches before coding UI (use Human MCP to generate visual mockups)
- âœ… **Mathematical Precision**: All design values (spacing, colors, font sizes, border radius) have clear mathematical reasoning and documented
- âœ… **Systematic Decisions**: Every design decision has documented reasoning, NOT arbitrary or "looks good"
- âœ… **Organic Animations**: Animations must be natural with varied timing (20s, 25s, 30s), NOT uniform/robotic (all same speed)
- âœ… **Attention to Detail**: Meticulous with every pixel, contrast ratio (WCAG AA/AAA), touch targets (44px minimum), accessibility

### **3. Project Organization**

- âœ… **Clean Workspace**: Cleanup regularly after each task completion, remove unused files/imports/dependencies
- âœ… **Structured Folders**: Follow standard architecture (src/components, src/hooks, src/lib, etc.), logical file organization
- âœ… **Consistent Naming**: File names (kebab-case), variable names (camelCase), function names (camelCase), component names (PascalCase) with clear convention
- âœ… **No Garbage Files**: ABSOLUTELY NO auto-generated docs, backup files (.backup, .old, .temp), log files, cache files
- âœ… **Professional .gitignore**: Properly configured to prevent garbage files, node_modules, .env, build artifacts
- âœ… **Clean Root Directory**: Root ONLY contains essential config files, NO scattered scripts/tests/docs (see Section 3.1)

